  "notes": [
    {
      "title": "The Six Nouns (الأسماء الستة)",
      "titleArabic": "الأسماء الستة",
      "content": [
        "Arabic has six special nouns that have unique case endings when attached to a possessive pronoun (except ي).",
        "These six nouns are: أَبٌ (father), أَخٌ (brother), حَمٌ (father-in-law), فَمٌ (mouth), ذُو (possessor of), and هَنٌ (a thing)."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "أَبٌ - father (becomes أَبُو، أَبَا، أَبِي when possessed)",
        "أَخٌ - brother (becomes أَخُو، أَخَا، أَخِي when possessed)",
        "حَمٌ - father-in-law (becomes حَمُو، حَمَا، حَمِي when possessed)",
        "فَمٌ - mouth (becomes فُو، فَا، فِي when possessed)",
        "ذُو - possessor of (only appears in genitive construction)",
        "هَنٌ - a thing (rare, euphemistic)"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "جَاءَ أَبُو مُحَمَّدٍ", "english": "Muhammad's father came" },
        { "arabic": "هَذَا أَخُو عَلِيٍّ", "english": "This is Ali's brother" },
        { "arabic": "رَأَيْتُ حَمَاهَا", "english": "I saw her father-in-law" },
        { "arabic": "هُوَ ذُو مَالٍ", "english": "He is a possessor of wealth" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Conditions for Special Declension",
      "titleArabic": "شروط إعراب الأسماء الستة بالحروف",
      "content": [
        "For these nouns to take their special endings, they must meet certain conditions.",
        "They must be singular, attached to a possessive pronoun other than ي, and not in the diminutive form."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Must be singular (not dual or plural)",
        "Must be in genitive construction (مضاف)",
        "The possessive cannot be ي (my)",
        "Without these conditions, they decline normally"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "جَاءَ أَبُوكَ", "english": "Your father came (special: و)" },
        { "arabic": "جَاءَ أَبِي", "english": "My father came (normal: ي pronoun)" },
        { "arabic": "جَاءَ الأَبُ", "english": "The father came (normal: no possession)" },
        { "arabic": "جَاءَ أَبَوَانِ", "english": "Two fathers came (normal: dual)" }
      ]
    }
  ],
